# Pipeline Studio

Kanon: [`docs/pipeline-studio/ARCHITECTURE.md`](../../docs/pipeline-studio/ARCHITECTURE.md) · PMIR: [`docs/evaluations/2026-06-19-pipeline-studio-pmir.md`](../../docs/evaluations/2026-06-19-pipeline-studio-pmir.md)

## MUST

- Varje Flow Tool Definition (FTD) har `toolId`, `silo`, `callable`, `schemaModule`, smoke commands
- Kör `npm run pipeline:validate` före merge som rör FTD eller `functions/src/schemas/`
- Scheman lever i `functions/src/schemas/` — callables importerar därifrån
- Extern AI Studio-paste → klassificera APPROVED / REJECTED innan implementation
- `pipeline_runs` append-only — metadata only, no PII
- Deploy: named function `recordPipelineRun` om callable ändras

## MUST NOT

- Genkit V1 runtime utan upphävd PMIR-stopp
- LLM Gemini tools som skriver WORM
- Cross-RAG i Flow-nodgraf (U1)
- Bypass `smoke:locked-ux` för Valv/Familjen UI-ändringar
- Hardkoda prompts utanför `sharedRules.ts` (befintlig backend-agents regel)

## CLI

```bash
npm run pipeline:validate [-- toolId]
npm run pipeline:export -- <toolId>
npm run pipeline:cursor-pack -- <toolId>
npm run pipeline:worktree -- <toolId>
npm run pipeline:run-smoke -- <toolId>
```

